author: D M
title: Fry-Angle Aquarium Society Fish Show Tomorrow
text:
October 9, 2015 | 0 Comments 
The Bermuda Fry-Angle Aquarium Society will stage its Annual Fish Show tomorrow [Oct 10] with the support of the SPCA hosting at it’s Valley Road, Paget location from 11am until 4pm. The Society is an organisation of individuals whose common interest is the keeping of tropical fish. 
A spokesperson said, “With over 65 entries encompassing a cross section of fresh water fish kept by local enthusiasts you can find junior and adult entries from African and South American Cichlids to guppies and even a Bichir Eel. 
“People wanting to find out more about the club and joining are invited to stop by for this free event open to the whole community.” Judging takes place today with the winners announced at a presentation tonight.
